FILEUTIL(3l)               LDG Call                    FILEUTIL(3l)

NAME
    FILEUTIL - A LDG library providing some utilities to copy,
               move and delete files and directories.

DESCRIPTION
    FileUtil is a LDG (Gem Dynamical Library) usefull to manipulate 
    files like in a installer program for instance. It provides 5 
    functions to copy, move and delete file and directories. These 
    functions try to be a equivalent functions of standard Unix
    commands such as cp, mv, rm, rmdir and mkdir.

SYNOPSIS
    WORD cp( char *src, char *dest);

        copy file(s) src in dest directory. TOS regular expression 
        can be used. A directory cannnot be copied. The function 
        returns number of file copied or a negative code error.

    WORD mv( char *src, char *dest);

        move file(s) src in dest directory. TOS regular expression 
        can be used. A directory cannnot be moved. The function 
        returns number of file moved or a negative code error.

    WORD rm( char *path);

        delete file(s) dest. TOS regular expression can be used. A 
        directory cannnot be deleted. The function returns number of 
        file deleted or a negative code error.

    WORD rmdir( char *path);

        delete directorie(s) dest. TOS regular expression can be used.
        A directory must be empty to be deleted. The function returns 
        number of directories deleted or a negative code error.

    WORD mkdir( char *path);

        create a directory. If a father directory does not existe it will
        be created too. The function returns number of directories 
        effectively created or a negative code error.

LOW LEVEL FUNCTIONS
	WORD regexp( const char *rexp, const char *name);
	
		returns TRUE if 'name' matches to the TOS regular expression 
		'rexp'. Special character are :
			* : design any group of characters,
			? : design any character,
			[] : design
		
	XDTA *fgetdta( void);
		
		returns the current XDTA (extended Disk Transfer Address).
		The XDTA structure is just an extension of the GEMDOS DTA
		structure. It can handle 64-bit filename buffer. This
		function replaces Fgetdta().
	
	void gsetdta( XDTA *);
	
		set the current XDTA. This function replaces Fsetdta().
	
	WORD fsfirst( char *name, LONG attr);
		
		This function replace Fsfirst() and works correctly with long
		filename.

	WORD fsnext( void);
	
		This function replace Fsnext() and works correctly with long
		filename.

BUGS
	Regexp() does not handle a sequence with * followed by a [] 
	sequence.
		

BINDING
    #define BIND_FILETUTIL	/* constant to define if the module is the main module */
    #include <ldg\fileutil.h>

    LDG *fu = ldg_open( "fileutil.ldg", ldg_global);
    if( fu) ldg_init_fileutil( fu);

HISTORIC
	version 0.10 : First public released version.
	version 0.20 : Shells function suppport now long filename.
				   New functions, extending GEMDOS functions
				   Fgetdta, Fsetdta, Fsfirst and Fsnext to long filename.
				   Adding regexp() function handling the TOS
				   regular expressions.
	
